{
  "texts": [
    "So, sometimes I feel like they would not request and say things and they would just accept what we are giving them.\"",
    "Some participants (P5, P12) in academic labs reflected that they encountered resistance to new tools in general: \"I feel like there is some inertia in the scientific community to switch to a different tool as widely used as IGV and genome browsers.\"",
    "In some cases, peers questioned the effectiveness of novel approaches, or there were language gaps between disciplines, therefore being barriers to trying new things.",
    "\"My PI doesn't like [Circos visualizations], he called them circles of hell because he's a clinician [...]\" P9 said.",
    "Furthermore, P9 shared that there could be problems with jargon and abstractions: \"[the documentation for these plots] is more from a visualization point of view, not from a genomic point of view."
  ]
}